8886554.jpg","cap":"National Scenic Byway Mohawk Towpath (New York)","desc":"","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:National_Scenic_Byway_-_Mohawk_Towpath_(New_York)_-_NARA_-_68886554.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/71/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Entering_Crescent_-_NARA_-_7720463.jpg/1280px-Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Entering_Crescent_-_NARA_-_7720463.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/71/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Entering_Crescent_-_NARA_-_7720463.jpg","cap":"Mohawk Towpath Byway Entering Crescent","desc":"This view welcomes visitors to the historical district of Crescent. Location: Crescent, New York Status: Public domain.","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Entering_Crescent_-_NARA_-_7720463.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/02/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Winter_Exploration_-_NARA_-_7720469.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/02/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Winter_Exploration_-_NARA_-_7720469.jpg","cap":"Mohawk Towpath Byway Winter Exploration","desc":"A man and his dog walk beneath bare branches on a clear snowy day. A century ago there would have been no trees or brush on the right side of this towpath. The bank of the Erie Canal was clear for boat tow lines. Location: New York Status: Public domain. Shenendehowa Nordic Club","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Winter_Exploration_-_NARA_-_7720469.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0c/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Birdwatchers_in_Autumn_-_NARA_-_7720460.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0c/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Birdwatchers_in_Autumn_-_NARA_-_7720460.jpg","cap":"Mohawk Towpath Byway Birdwatchers in Autumn","desc":"A group of avid birdwatchers enjoys a peaceful afternoon on a trail laden with fall foliage. Location: Waterford, New York Status: Public domain. Photo courtesy of Eric J Hamilton.","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Birdwatchers_in_Autumn_-_NARA_-_7720460.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/63/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Canoeing_on_a_Colorful_Day_-_NARA_-_7720470.jpg/1280px-Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Canoeing_on_a_Colorful_Day_-_NARA_-_7720470.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/63/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Canoeing_on_a_Colorful_Day_-_NARA_-_7720470.jpg","cap":"Mohawk Towpath Byway Canoeing on a Colorful Day","desc":"A woman paddles a canoe up the Mohawk River amidst a colorful array of fall foliage. Location: Halfmoon, New York Status: Public domain. Photo by Eric J Hamilton.","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Canoeing_on_a_Colorful_Day_-_NARA_-_7720470.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7a/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Children_and_Sheep_at_Clifton_Park%27s_Farm_Fest_-_NARA_-_7720461.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7a/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Children_and_Sheep_at_Clifton_Park%27s_Farm_Fest_-_NARA_-_7720461.jpg","cap":"Mohawk Towpath Byway Children and Sheep at Clifton Park's Farm Fest","desc":"Two children observe sheep enclosed in a wooden pen during Clifton Park's Farm Fest in New York. Location: Clifton Park, New York Status: Public domain. Larry Syzdek, photographer","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Children_and_Sheep_at_Clifton_Park%27s_Farm_Fest_-_NARA_-_7720461.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b3/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Gold_and_Green_-_NARA_-_7720471.jpg/1280px-Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Gold_and_Green_-_NARA_-_7720471.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b3/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Gold_and_Green_-_NARA_-_7720471.jpg","cap":"Mohawk Towpath Byway Gold and Green","desc":"On Peebles Island, a beautiful mix of gold and green serves as a shimmering reminder of the majesty of autumn. Location: Waterford, New York Status: Public domain. Photo by Henrietta O'Grady.","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Gold_and_Green_-_NARA_-_7720471.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Grooms_Tavern_-_NARA_-_7720464.jpg/1280px-Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Grooms_Tavern_-_NARA_-_7720464.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8c/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Grooms_Tavern_-_NARA_-_7720464.jpg","cap":"Mohawk Towpath Byway Grooms Tavern","desc":"Automobiles from many decades line up outside Grooms Tavern, an important historic site in Clifton Park. Location: Clifton Park, New York Status: Public domain. Photo by Eric Hamilton","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Grooms_Tavern_-_NARA_-_7720464.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d9/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Hamlet_of_Vischer_Ferry_-_NARA_-_7720473.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d9/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Hamlet_of_Vischer_Ferry_-_NARA_-_7720473.jpg","cap":"Mohawk Towpath Byway Hamlet of Vischer Ferry","desc":"Autumn comes to a street before a white steepled church in Vischer Ferry. The Vischer Ferry Historic District was originally settled in 1671. Construction of the Erie Canal in the 1820s brought more residents to the community, many worked at the dry dock, hotel or other services required along the canal. Boat builders used Greek Revival patterns when they constructed their own homes in the village","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Hamlet_of_Vischer_Ferry_-_NARA_-_7720473.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Historic_Canal_Towpath_-_NARA_-_7720468.jpg/1280px-Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Historic_Canal_Towpath_-_NARA_-_7720468.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/24/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Historic_Canal_Towpath_-_NARA_-_7720468.jpg","cap":"Mohawk Towpath Byway Historic Canal Towpath","desc":"Horses once used these well-worn towpaths to haul barges along the canal, but today they form a network of trails throughout the region. Location: New York Status: Public domain. Photo by Eric Hamilton","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Historic_Canal_Towpath_-_NARA_-_7720468.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/85/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Historic_Erie_Canal_Photo-_Aqueduct_over_the_Mohawk_River_-_NARA_-_7720466.jpg/1280px-Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Historic_Erie_Canal_Photo-_Aqueduct_over_the_Mohawk_River_-_NARA_-_7720466.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/85/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Historic_Erie_Canal_Photo-_Aqueduct_over_the_Mohawk_River_-_NARA_-_7720466.jpg","cap":"Mohawk Towpath Byway Historic Erie Canal Photo Aqueduct over the Mohaw","desc":"This photo shows the early years of the Erie Canal as its stone aqueduct passes through Rexford. Location: Rexford, New York Status: Public domain. Original of this photograph is in the Clifton Park Collection","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Historic_Erie_Canal_Photo-_Aqueduct_over_the_Mohawk_River_-_NARA_-_7720466.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Peebles_Island_-_NARA_-_7720472.jpg/1280px-Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Peebles_Island_-_NARA_-_7720472.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/37/Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Peebles_Island_-_NARA_-_7720472.jpg","cap":"Mohawk Towpath Byway Peebles Island","desc":"From Peebles Island, the Mohawk River creates a beautiful contrast to the red and orange trees lining the riverbank. Location: Waterford, New York Status: Public domain. Photo by Henrietta O'Grady.","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mohawk_Towpath_Byway_-_Peebles_Island_-_NARA_-_7720472.jpg"}]}